						               													<description>Inspired by the game For the Queen, Rituels (french for &amp;quot;Rituals&amp;quot;), is a card-based story-building game that you and up to five other players can begin playing in minutes. Choose your cult and ritual, then use the prompt cards to collaboratively tell a story of love, betrayal, doubt, and devotion.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rituels will have you roam the lands of cultists trying to summon a creature capable of destroying the whole univers. But will all partakers go through with this plan till the end?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game suggests 8 Cults and 8 Rituals.&amp;#10;The prompt cards are divided in 2 decks: Act I (Why did the characters join the cult, what are their hopes and dreams?) and Act II (What are these nightmares troubling your sleep more and more as the day of the Ritual is getting closer? Are your teammates trustworthy? Are you really one the right side?).&amp;#10;A Final Act in a black envelop will have you secretly vote for the success or failure of the Ritual, ending the game one of three ways.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
